WHAT THIS COVERS

This licence covers the material created by Te Whare o Toitū AI: the text of
these pages, the leadership guidance attached to each night, the design, and
the code that calculates the dates.

It does not, and cannot, cover the maramataka itself. The maramataka is a
taonga handed down through generations of observation. It is not ours to
licence. Iwi and hapū hold their own maramataka, shaped by their own whenua,
moana, and mātauranga, and those forms take precedence in their own rohe.

PERMITTED USE

You are welcome to use, copy, share, and adapt this material for
non-commercial purposes, provided that you:

  - attribute it to Te Whare o Toitū AI, with a link to
    https://temaramataka.nz
  - do not misrepresent where it came from, and
  - carry these same terms with any copy or adaptation you share.

Non-commercial use includes personal practice; use with whānau, hapū, and
iwi; wānanga, classrooms, marae, and community settings; and internal use
within an organisation, whether or not that organisation is a business.

USE REQUIRING PERMISSION

Written permission is required before you:

  - sell this material, or anything derived from it
  - include it in a paid product, service, course, or application
  - use it in advertising, or to promote a commercial offering
  - republish it under another name, or in a way that obscures its origin.

Permission is not hard to obtain. Write to kupu@temaramataka.nz and ask.

NO WARRANTY

This material is provided as it is, without warranty of any kind, express or
implied. Dates are calculated from astronomical new moon times for Aotearoa
New Zealand and are offered as a guide, not a prescription. The tohu of your
own taiao always take precedence over this calendar. To the extent permitted
by law, Te Whare o Toitū AI accepts no liability arising from the use of this
material.

